Class ExperimentController

  • java.lang.Object
    • ExperimentController

  • public class ExperimentController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class serves as the test environment. Through use of this class the user may test the two types of lists, and the two sorting types. The user may also specify the number of iterations and how large the array will be.
    Author:
    Craig Lombardo

      • timeArrayInsertion

        public long timeArrayInsertion(int numberOfItems,
                               int seed)
        This method will be used to return the total amount of time taken for the computer to sort an ArrayList using insertion sort.
        Parameters:
        numberOfItems - This is an integer value of how many items will be added to the front of the list before sorting.
        seed - An integer value used to generate pseudorandom numbers.
        Returns:
        long This method returns a long which corresponds to the time taken,in ms, to sort the list.

      • runTimeArrayInsertion

        public java.lang.String runTimeArrayInsertion(int number)
        This method runs the method myTimeArrayInsertion a specified number of times. The program increments the number of added elements by 50000 each time. This method averages five runs of the returned values for myTimeArrayInsertion.
        Parameters:
        number - The number of trials to run.
        Returns:
        String The average run times of the tests, put in a format that is beneficial for use with .csv files.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        The main method is used so the program may be run through a console. This is beneficial as the output can easily be piped to a .csv file
        Parameters:
        args - Argument 1 (args[0]) is the test type, either "insertArray", "insertLinked", "shellArray" or "shellLinked" (no quatation marks). It is important to note that responses other than "array" or "linked" in all lowercase for the first argument will not lead to desired results.
